The apartment is at 25 square meters

14
00:00:46,871 --> 00:00:51,048
And Isabelle pays about SEK 4,900 in monthly rent.

15
00:00:51,048 --> 00:00:54,779
What she likes best about her apartment is that it is so close to the university,

16
00:00:54,779 --> 00:00:57,387
But also for gym and grocery stores.

17
00:01:00,502 --> 00:01:02,619
If you prefer to live more centrally

18
00:01:02,619 --> 00:01:05,811
Of course, it is also possible to live near the town.

19
00:01:09,116 --> 00:01:13,580
In this rental apartment lives Eva, which originally comes from Örebro

20
00:01:13,580 --> 00:01:15,648
But who still wanted to find something of its own.

21
00:01:16,199 --> 00:01:18,568
The apartment is 42 square meters

22
00:01:18,568 --> 00:01:20,890
And costs about SEK 5,000 in monthly rent.

23
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:27,103
Eva likes the proximity to the pulse and being able to go to town in just minutes

24
00:01:27,103 --> 00:01:29,156
And therefore enjoy the area very well.

25
